<subSubSection id="C3216579FFD6FFC1CA99C227201E6BFC" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8436F2FFD6FFC1CA99C227201E6BFC" blockId="7.[151,1437,1518,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
This species is distributed from the Iberian peninsula across central and southern Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1CE84C22725F46A0D" box="[1162,1239,1554,1580]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Russia</collectingCountry>
, Crimea and 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1CF62C22621CD6A71" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1CAF2C20320CF6A71" author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[252,492,1590,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD6FFC1CB7CC20220896A71" box="[370,426,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). As was stated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1C8CEC20D22AE6A70" author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[704,909,1590,1619]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD6FFC1C90CC20222116A71" box="[770,818,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, historical records of this species in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1CF2FC20324506A71" box="[1313,1395,1590,1616]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are rather scarce. The only exact locality, Bosiljevo, was given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1C974C26925656A54" author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[890,1094,1626,1655]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD6FFC1C9B5C26E22C86A55" box="[955,1003,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1CE5EC26F25C16A55" author="Rebel, H." box="[1104,1250,1626,1652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="97 - 377" refId="ref10440" refString="Rebel, H. (1904) Studien uber die Lepidopterenfauna der Balkanlander. II. Teil. Bosnien und Herzegowina. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 19, 97 - 377." type="journal article" year="1904">Rebel (1904)</bibRefCitation>
mentions it only for Dalmatia, a larger coastal region of 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1C877C24B23ED6AB9" box="[633,718,1662,1688]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, while 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1C913C24B22E06AB9" author="Stauder, H." box="[797,963,1662,1688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10678" refString="Stauder, H. (1921) Die Zygaenidenarmut der adriatischen Inseln. Societas entomologica, 36, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1921">Stauder (1921)</bibRefCitation>
mentions it from the coastal areas of 
<collectingRegion id="49FFF810FFD6FFC1CF6DC24B24BE6AB9" box="[1379,1437,1662,1688]" country="Croatia" name="Istarska" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Istria</collectingRegion>
and Dalmatia. During this survey the species was recorded on three localities with eight collected specimens (
<figureCitation id="13002A77FFD6FFC1CAC0C2F320316AC0" box="[206,274,1734,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,189,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-28@12.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Adscita geryon in Croatia based on newly collected data and historical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4643399/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). These are the first recent records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD6FFC1C8B4C2F222046AC1" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[698,807,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryon">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD6FFC1C8B4C2F222046AC1" box="[698,807,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1C944C2F322BF6AC1" box="[842,924,1734,1760]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
after almost a century (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1CEAAC2F3241F6AC1" author="Stauder, H." box="[1188,1340,1734,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10678" refString="Stauder, H. (1921) Die Zygaenidenarmut der adriatischen Inseln. Societas entomologica, 36, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1921">Stauder 1921</bibRefCitation>
) and the first ones with precise localities and collection dates. All three localities (two of them being very close one to another) are located within Lička Plješevica montane range at the border with 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1CE31C33B24666B09" box="[1087,1349,1806,1832]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Bosnia &amp; Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. This is a very diverse area in terms of butterfly diversity (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD6FFC1C90DC30722ED6B6D" author="Koren, T. &amp; Laus, B. &amp; Tvrtkovic, N. &amp; Verovnik, R." box="[771,974,1842,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="257 - 283" refId="ref9697" refString="Koren, T., Laus, B., Tvrtkovic, N. &amp; Verovnik, R. (2020) Butterfly diversity of Licka Pljesevica Mountain chain, Croatia (Lepi- doptera: Papilionoidea). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 48, 257 - 283." type="journal article" year="2020">
Koren 
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD6FFC1C95DC30622AF6B6D" box="[851,908,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) and seemingly also for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD6FFC1CF1DC30724BA6B6D" box="[1299,1433,1842,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zygaenidae</taxonomicName>
. This is a significant expanse of the known range in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1C90BC36322746B51" box="[773,855,1878,1904]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
as the record from Bosiljevo is distanced about 
<quantity id="4CC39B17FFD6FFC1CF7CC36321C96BB5" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" unit="km" value="140.0">140 km</quantity>
from Mt. Lička Plješevica. The discovered populations in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1C99EC34F22C16BB5" box="[912,994,1914,1940]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are probably connected to the ones in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD6FFC1CAC8C3AB20EE6B99" box="[198,461,1950,1976]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Bosnia &amp; Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. However, recent surveys on the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD6FFC1C949C3AB22E96B99" box="[839,970,1950,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zygaenidae</taxonomicName>
of the country are lacking so this cannot be proven.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3216579FFD9FFCECA99C4A224556DD4" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8436F2FFD9FFCECA99C4A224556DD4" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCECA99C4A2202E6C91" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[151,269,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryion">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCECA99C4A2202E6C91" box="[151,269,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also known from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD9FFCECBFBC4A2222A6C90" box="[501,777,151,177]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Bosnia and Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
from where 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCEC995C4A224106C90" authority="(Alberti, 1938)" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Alberti" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[923,1331,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryion" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCEC995C4A225A16C90" box="[923,1154,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion orientalis</emphasis>
(Alberti, 1938)
</taxonomicName>
has been described and the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD9FFCEC842C48E23BD6CF4" box="[588,670,187,213]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
most probably belong to this subspecies. Such records have already been hypothesized in the recent work (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B03FFD9FFCEC877C4D5221D6CDB" author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[633,830,223,251]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCEC8B3C4EA23CC6CD8" box="[701,751,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) when it was stated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCECE58C4EA241D6CD8" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Alberti" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[1110,1342,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryion" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCECE58C4EA241D6CD8" box="[1110,1342,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Bosnian Mountains (Makljen pass) but must occur in more parts of the Dinaric Alps. This has now been confirmed with this survey. Habitats on which 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCEC931C51222906D61" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" box="[831,947,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryion">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCEC931C51222906D61" box="[831,947,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded are large montane grasslands, which were once used for cattle grazing but are nowadays mostly abandoned. As the species was collected in several different years, it seems that the population is present and possibly numerous. Even after this survey, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCECAC8C5A620106D8D" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[198,307,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryon">
<emphasis id="B94FEAE0FFD9FFCECAC8C5A620106D8D" box="[198,307,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">A. geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the rarest 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D71FFD9FFCEC82AC5A623866D8C" authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1828" box="[548,677,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Procridinae">Procridinae</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD9FFCEC92FC5A622506D8C" box="[801,883,403,429]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
and additional efforts should be taken in order to map its distribution and asses its conservation status. Additional surveys are needed on other high mountains of 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7662FFD9FFCECAC8C5EE20386DD4" box="[198,283,475,501]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, especially Velebit and Dinara in order to additionally explore the distribution range of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
